title: The Batman
items: {'publisher': 'Slant Magazine', 'author': 'Jake Cole', 'link': '', 'rate': '75', 'content': 'The film stands apart for thoughtfully suggesting that Batman might actually one day make Gotham a better place, and not merely a safer one'}

title: The Batman
items: {'publisher': 'TheWrap', 'author': 'Todd Gilchrist', 'link': 'https://www.thewrap.com/the-batman-review-robert-pattinson-zoe-kravitz/', 'rate': '88', 'content': 'With Pattinson glowering beneath his cowl, Reeves creates a Batman whose psychology is at least as interesting as his crime-fighting activities, for the first time in a long time.'}

title: Eternals
items: {'publisher': 'Slashfilm', 'author': 'Hoai-Tran Bui', 'link': 'https://www.slashfilm.com/641297/eternals-review-a-wildly-ambitious-but-tonally-uneven-cosmic-epic/', 'rate': '65', 'content': "With Eternals, Marvel turns a risky gamble into another piece of the puzzle. Its cosmic ambitions, its prevailing humanism amid a nihilistic outlook, and its gestures at maturity — the (real!) sex scene, the depth and warmth that they give to Henry's LGBTQ relationship — are not enough to make Eternals more than just another film to fit neatly in the Marvel Studios mold. But even so, Zhao brings an elegance to the film and the cast bring a vulnerability and care to their characters that leave a lingering impression, even as the last super-punch fades."}

title: Eternals
items: {'publisher': 'BBC', 'author': 'Nicholas Barber', 'link': 'https://www.bbc.com/culture/article/20211024-three-stars-for-chlo-zhaos-disappointing-eternals', 'rate': '60', 'content': "Eternals is more serious in tone and more deliberate in its pacing than the average Marvel movie, with less of the usual banter and no cameo appearances by other superheroes. But, if you're looking for the humanity and originality of Zhao's other films, you won't find much of it here."}

title: House of Gucci
items: {'publisher': 'Variety', 'author': 'Owen Gleiberman', 'link': 'https://variety.com/2021/film/reviews/house-of-gucci-review-lady-gaga-adam-driver-al-pacino-jared-leto-ridley-scott-1235112936/', 'rate': '80', 'content': 'House of Gucci is an icepick docudrama that has a great deal of fun with its grand roster of ambitious scoundrels, but it’s never less than a straight-faced and nimbly accomplished movie.'}

title: House of Gucci
items: {'publisher': 'The Film Stage', 'author': 'Matt Cipolla', 'link': '', 'rate': '50', 'content': 'Despite the reasons House of Gucci doesn’t work, none are damning enough to make a bad movie. It’s forgettable, sometimes playing like the sort of cable-TV fare that displaced these tales from the silver screen over the past decade. Yet Scott’s efforts, and especially those of Johnson and Bentivegna, just don’t keep up. And what’s the point of going big if you’re not going to go for it all?'}

title: West Side Story
items: {'publisher': 'Slashfilm', 'author': 'Chris Evangelista', 'link': 'https://www.slashfilm.com/674685/west-side-story-review-steven-spielbergs-big-vibrant-take-on-the-classic-musical-is-one-of-his-best-films', 'rate': '95', 'content': "Spielberg's West Side Story is a knock-out. title: West Side Story
items: {'publisher': 'Empire', 'author': "Helen O'Hara", 'link': 'https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/west-side-story-2021/', 'rate': '100', 'content': 'Heartfelt and heart-breaking, this feels like Spielberg has made an adaptation faithful to its roots but also, always, alive to the modern world.'}

title: Cruella

title: Cruella
items: {'publisher': 'Entertainment Weekly', 'author': 'Leah Greenblatt', 'link': 'https://ew.com/movies/movie-reviews/cruella-movie-review/', 'rate': '67', 'content': 'Cruella comes off as a curious animal, eager to change its spots and trying a little bit of everything along the way.'}

title: Free Guy
items: {'publisher': 'IGN', 'author': 'Kristy Puchko', 'link': '', 'rate': '70', 'content': 'Free Guy delivers a first hour that is outrageously entertaining, stuffed with gonzo action, goofy gags, star power, big ideas, and plenty of Easter Eggs for lovers of movies and video games. However, in its second half, the joyful journey is derailed by a slog of a side quest, falling short of the potential set-up.'}

title: Free Guy
items: {'publisher': 'IndieWire', 'author': 'David Ehrlich', 'link': 'https://www.indiewire.com/2021/08/free-guy-review-1234655686/', 'rate': '50', 'content': 'Free Guy is nothing if not a movie that wins you over in spite of your better judgment and best defenses, but its “be the change you wish to see in the world” energy feels like a micro-transactional smokescreen for a corporate monoculture that only values creativity so far as it can be used to fool us into paying for things we already own.'}

title: Luca

title: Belfast

title: Black Widow

title: Turning Red
items: {'publisher': 'Empire', 'author': 'Ben Travis', 'link': 'https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/turning-red/', 'rate': '80', 'content': 'A daring, distinctive and downright delightful debut from Domee Shi, and a welcome change of pace from Pixar. title: Turning Red
items: {'publisher': 'The Globe and Mail (Toronto)', 'author': 'Barry Hertz', 'link': 'https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/film/reviews/article-turning-red-is-top-tier-pixar-no-matter-your-love-or-hate-for-toronto/', 'rate': '90', 'content': 'This is an energetic, heartfelt, poignant and often delightfully subversive story of one young girl’s path into adulthood, and embrace of her cultural heritage.'}

title: The Card Counter

title: The Card Counter

title: Dune

items: {'publisher': 'Film Threat', 'author': '', 'link': '', 'rate': '90', 'content': 'Us is a bit predictable and contains a few jumbled auditory edits. title: Tenet
items: {'publisher': 'IndieWire', 'author': 'Mike McCahill', 'link': 'https://www.indiewire.com/2020/08/tenet-review-1234581454/', 'rate': '42', 'content': 'What kind of picture is it? It’s clever, too — yes, the palindromic title has some narrative correlation — albeit in an exhausting, rather joyless way. As second comings go, Tenet is like witnessing a Sermon on the Mount preached by a savior who speaks exclusively in dour, drawn-out riddles. Any awe is flattened by follow-up questions.'}

title: The King of Staten Island

title: Toy Story 4

title: The Irishman
